{
  "stem": "21786.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then I had a brother-- then I had an uncle who died in Russia during the First World War being in the Czech army.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "His name was Rudolph.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I was named after him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In fact, I was named originally Walter, W-A-L-T-E-R.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But my mother realized that she made a mistake.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And when I was one and a half years old, through the order of parliament, my name was changed to Rudolph.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother's name was Franzisca, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] written F-R-A-N-Z-I-S-C-A.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was a very motherly type.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her maiden name was Spitz, S-P-I-T-Z.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hannah, I think, was her name, her Jewish name, which I just found out, which was not used.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was a very kind person, a very kind of determined person.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When she made up her mind, it was very difficult to change it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] she went through Terezin and through Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She passed the selection.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, interestingly enough, after the war, I waited whether she would return.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then, at the beginning of July, I see myself typing a letter to my aunt in-- who lived at that point in New York-- describing a little bit our fate, what happened about till that point.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I said that my mother supposedly left Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But as she did not report or there are any-- and there are no news about her up until this point in time, I have to take for granted that she-- and I didn't write the word died, for somebody rang the bell.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I opened the door, it was mother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Fine.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Perfect, go ahead.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
